vision.voltsofdoom.coresystem.loading.registry

Class Registry

  • java.lang.Object
    • vision.voltsofdoom.coresystem.loading.registry.Registry

  • public class Registry
extends java.lang.Object
    The Registry is a central repository of Suppliers of game objects (characterised by IRegistryEntry). These objects are divided into IRegistrys by their type (Parameterised of IRegistryEntry and IRegistry)

    How the Registry is created:
    1. New RegistryTypes are created with the RegistryEvent.CreateRegistryTypesEvent
    2. TypeRegistrys are collected with the RegistryEvent.CreateAndSubmitRegistriesEvent. These should be created in the course of this Event.
    3. TypeRegistrys are populated during the RegistryEvent.PopulateTypeRegistriesEvent. They are not necessarily required to be populated in this Event, though for simplicity and organisation's sake, and to prevent any loading errors with custom, uncreated RegistryTypes, and because it is the convention, TypeRegistrys should be populated during this Event.
    4. Every unique type of TypeRegistry registered is collected into a Set of unique IRegistryEntrys.
    5. A RegistryEvent.RegisterTypeEvent event is called for each collected type. A FinalisedTypeRegistry is created for the Event's type, and every TypeRegistry of that type registers/adds its contents to that FinalisedTypeRegistry. This results in there being one FinalisedTypeRegistry for each type of IRegistryEntry that is being registered.
    Author:
    GenElectrovise
